  "text": "This audit identified 18 Java source files implementing or defining Access Control List (ACL) authorization logic in Apache Kafka. The files are organized across three main packages:\n\n## Core Authorizer Interface (clients/src/main/)\nThe primary Authorizer interface is defined in `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/authorizer/Authorizer.java`. This is a pluggable interface that brokers use for authorization decisions. Key supporting types in this package include:\n- `AuthorizerServerInfo.java`: Provides runtime broker metadata to authorizers during startup\n- `AuthorizableRequestContext.java`: Interface for request context with authentication and connection details\n- `Action.java`: Represents an action being authorized with operation and resource pattern\n- `AuthorizationResult.java`: Enum for authorization decisions (ALLOWED/DENIED)\n- `AclCreateResult.java`: Result wrapper for ACL creation operations\n- `AclDeleteResult.java`: Result wrapper for ACL deletion operations\n\n## Authorizer Utilities (server/src/main/)\nUtility classes for authorization are located in `server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/security/authorizer/`:\n- `AclEntry.java`: Utility class defining supported operations per resource type and authorization error codes\n- `AuthorizerUtils.java`: Factory utility for creating Authorizer plugin instances\n\nAdditionally, `clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/AuthorizerNotReadyException.java` provides an exception type for when authorizers are not ready to process requests.\n\n## Built-in Implementation (metadata/src/main/)\nThe KRaft-based metadata log implementation is in `metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/authorizer/`:\n- `StandardAuthorizer.java`: Main implementation storing ACLs in the metadata log, implementing both ClusterMetadataAuthorizer and Monitorable interfaces\n- `ClusterMetadataAuthorizer.java`: Interface extending Authorizer with methods for KRaft-based clusters (loadSnapshot, addAcl, removeAcl, setAclMutator)\n- `AclMutator.java`: Interface implemented by QuorumController for ACL create/delete operations\n- `AclCache.java`: Immutable cache storing ACLs indexed by UUID and sorted by resource\n- `StandardAcl.java`: Represents a single Kafka ACL identified by UUID\n- `StandardAclWithId.java`: Tuple pairing UUID with StandardAcl\n- `StandardAclRecordIterator.java`: Iterator for ACL records in batches\n- `StandardAuthorizerData.java`: Holds the current ACL data state\n\n## Authorization Type Summary\n- **Interface definitions**: Authorizer, AuthorizerServerInfo, AuthorizableRequestContext, ClusterMetadataAuthorizer, AclMutator\n- **Implementations**: StandardAuthorizer (implements ClusterMetadataAuthorizer and Authorizer)\n- **Support classes**: Action, AuthorizationResult, AclCreateResult, AclDeleteResult, AclEntry, AuthorizerUtils, AclCache, StandardAcl, StandardAclWithId, StandardAclRecordIterator, StandardAuthorizerData\n- **Exception types**: AuthorizerNotReadyException"
